										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.vastdata.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">VAST Data</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> has officially ascended to a $30 billion </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/cloudsmith-raises-72m-to-secure-the-ai-software-supply-chain/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">valuation</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. This comes after a massive $1 billion strategic injection led by NVIDIA. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This newly raised round triples VAST Data&#8217;s valuation at the end of 2023, which was considered high even when it was average for an era where &#8220;AI infrastructure&#8221; was the hottest injection site for venture capital and enterprise giants.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The New Architecture of Intelligence</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">For decades, data storage was seen as a commodity, a passive &#8220;locker&#8221; for digital information. VAST Data upended this narrative by building a &#8220;Data Platform&#8221; specifically designed for the massive throughput requirements of deep learning and generative AI.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By eliminating the traditional tiers of storage and creating a unified, flash-based architecture, VAST has allowed companies to feed data to GPUs at unprecedented speeds. NVIDIA’s $1 billion injection isn&#8217;t just a financial endorsement; it is a tactical integration. </span></p>
<div id="attachment_200280" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200280" class="size-large wp-image-200280" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Data-1024x683.jpg" alt="Data" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-200280" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">As NVIDIA transitions from a chipmaker to a full-stack data centre provider, VAST Data’s software has become the de facto nervous system for the NVIDIA DGX SuperPOD environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We are moving past the era of simple storage,&#8221; said Renen Hallak, CEO and founder of VAST Data. &#8220;Our partnership with NVIDIA allows us to bridge the gap between raw information and actionable intelligence. We aren&#8217;t just storing bits, we are organising the world&#8217;s data so that AI can actually understand it in real-time.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/cloudsmith-raises-72m-to-secure-the-ai-software-supply-chain/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Cloudsmith Raises $72M to Secure the AI Software Supply Chain</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Why NVIDIA is Doubling Down</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NVIDIA’s decision to lead a $1 billion round is a rare move for a company that typically prefers smaller, ecosystem-seeding investments. But, for modern-day AI, the bottleneck is no longer beyond compute; it’s data starvation. GPUs of high order have to wait around idling while some old storage infrastructure gets after a huge dataset to train LLMs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By backing VAST Data, NVIDIA ensures that its hardware customers have access to a storage layer that can keep pace. The investment also suggests a deeper software integration. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Market analysts speculate that VAST’s Data Engine will soon be natively optimised for NVIDIA’s CUDA architecture, creating a &#8220;walled garden&#8221; of high-performance AI infrastructure.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The &#8220;NVIDIA Premium&#8221; and Market Impact</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $30 billion valuation puts VAST Data in the rare atmosphere of &#8220;decacorns&#8221;, outstripping many established publicly traded storage companies. </span>This &#8220;NVIDIA Premium&#8221; reflects a market trend where companies in the AI supply chain see value skyrocket. Competitors like Pure Storage and NetApp race to modernise stacks, but VAST Data has a significant head start.</p>
