<h3><b>2. Use clear risk limits</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always define stop-loss levels, take-profit rules, and position sizing before activating automation.</span></p>
<h3><b>3. Avoid changing too many variables at once</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you constantly change strategy settings, timeframes, and assets at the same time, you will not know what caused the results.</span></p>
<h3><b>4. Keep your strategy simple at first</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A simple, well-tested strategy is often more effective than a complicated one that you do not fully understand.</span></p>
<h3><b>5. Do not treat AI as a guarantee</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">AI can improve efficiency, but it cannot eliminate market risk. Good judgment and discipline still matter.</span></p>
<h2><b>Pros and Cons of Free AI Trading Bots</b></h2>
<h3><b>Advantages</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Free AI trading bots make it easier for beginners to explore automation without major financial commitment. They can improve discipline, reduce emotional trading, and help identify short-term market opportunities more efficiently.</span></p>
<h3><b>Limitations</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Free plans may come with restricted features, limited exchange access, or fewer advanced tools. More importantly, even the best bot can perform poorly if the strategy is weak or if risk management is ignored.</span></p>
<h2><b>Final Thoughts</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The market for AI trading bots in 2026 includes a wide range of options for beginner intraday traders. Whether you want simple automation, strategy templates, copy trading, or deeper customization, there are now several free or low-cost tools that can help you get started.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Among them, </span><b>BitsStrategy</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is one of several platforms designed for beginners exploring AI trading tools</span><b>. </b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> It offers a more practical balance between strategy learning, automation, and intraday trading usability, which may be relevant for first-time users. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The most important thing to remember is this: an AI trading bot is a tool, not a shortcut to guaranteed profits. Long-term success still depends on strategy quality, risk control, and continuous learning.</span></p>
<h2><b>FAQ</b></h2>
<h3><b>Are free AI trading bots good for beginners?</b></h3>
